AUDIO: 'Hi there, Mara here. In this video, I\'ll show you how to turn a set of photos into a shareable video using [music] the Captions app. Videos perform better than photos right now across pretty much every social platform, but that doesn\'t mean you always have the time or energy'

[00:14] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'to film something. The good news is you don\'t always have to. Whether [music] it\'s product shots, vacation photos, or just pictures sitting in your camera roll, apps like Captions can take those photos and use AI to turn them into a'

[00:27] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'fully edited video complete with script, voiceover, transitions, and music. Here\'s how to do it. Start by clicking the link in the description below to open up the Captions app. [music] From the main screen, go to the voiceover'

[00:40] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'drop-down, tap the paperclip, then media. Then tap all the photos you want to import from your camera roll. From there, drop in a brief description of what you want your video to be about. Just a sentence or two is enough. You'

[00:53] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'can also choose a video style, which tells Captions how to auto edit it &gt;&gt; [music] &gt;&gt; with transitions, zooms, music, and more. Captions will then generate you a video plan to review. It\'ll write a script and generate a voiceover, which'

[01:06] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'you can edit to adjust the story and the narrator voice. [music] You can also use this screen to preset your preferred editing style, colors, and effects. Next, just tap create project [music]'

[01:18] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'to generate your video. It\'ll take just a few minutes to create, and Captions will notify you when your video is ready to review. When it is ready, you\'ll see your photos playing back video timeline with edits already applied. You can also'

[01:30] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'keep customizing your video, adding captions, swapping music, and adjusting anything else you want. When you\'re done, just export [music] and post. And that\'s all it takes. You can create a'

[01:42] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'full video from your pictures with no filming and no complicated [music] editing. I hope this tutorial was helpful. Make sure to like and subscribe for more content just like this. I\'ll see you in the next'
